    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/feature-table-alignment-and-integration/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "On the other side (Figure 1A2), it is also possible to start the process from an aligned feature intensity table (.csv file) and corresponding MS/MS spectra file (.mgf file)... In this case, the occurrence of each peak and loss within a given sample is counted using the feature intensity table to determine whether a feature is detected or not into the sample (Figure 1A2).",
      "asbval:note": "Core workflow described in paper; MemoMatrix construction from aligned feature tables and MS2 spectra is explicitly documented.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "feature-table-alignment-and-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Integrate aligned feature tables with their corresponding MS2 spectra to construct a MemoMatrix\u2014a sample-by-MS2-fingerprint matrix that enables retention-time-agnostic sample comparison.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:00:17.499910+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/feature-table-alignment-and-integration/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The MEMO strategy exploits the advantages of LC, namely its separative power (thus simplifying the chemical complexity of the analyzed sample and allowing isomerism resolving) while avoiding the caveats of a RT based alignment since the MEMO vectors only contain mass spectrometric information.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly states MEMO vectors are RT-agnostic and avoid RT-based alignment.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "feature-table-alignment-and-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "retention-time-agnostic sample comparison",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:00:17.499910+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/feature-table-alignment-and-integration/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Spectra were processed using memo_ms package (0.1.3) and the following parameters for spectra import were used: min_relative_intensity: 0.01, max_relative_intensity: 1, min_peaks_required: 10, losses_from: 10, losses_to: 200, n_decimals: 2.",
      "asbval:note": "memo_ms v0.1.3 explicitly used for processing spectra and constructing MEMO matrices from aligned samples.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "feature-table-alignment-and-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "memo-ms tool with role: Executes memo_from_aligned function to count MS2 peaks and neutral losses and construct the MemoMatrix",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:00:17.499910+00:00",
