      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/memo-ms-api-usage-and-parameter-configuration/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In this case, the occurrence of each peak and loss within a given sample is counted using the feature intensity table to determine whether a feature is detected or not into the sample (Figure 1A2). Note here that it is not the intensity table of the MS1 feature (peak intensity or area) that is considered but rather a simple presence/absence matrix. This 'MEMO from aligned samples' workflow can conveniently complement pre-existing metabolomics data treatment pipelines (Figure 1A2).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms aligned feature tables and MS2 spectra are inputs, but specifies MGF format explicitly: 'the only required input is a .mgf file for each sample (Mascot Generic Format, a text format commonly used to report fragmentation mass spectrometry data)' (passage 7). mzML is not mentioned as an input format for memo-ms in the provided passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "memo-ms-api-usage-and-parameter-configuration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Aligned feature tables (CSV format) with corresponding MS2 spectra data (MGF or mzML files)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:01:28.015884+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/memo-ms-api-usage-and-parameter-configuration/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Documents are then aggregated by summing peaks and losses occurrences across spectra of a given sample to obtain the MEMO vector (Figure 1B). Samples' MEMO vectors can then be aligned to obtain a MEMO matrix (Figure 1C).",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes MEMO vectors as aggregations of peak and loss occurrences per sample.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "memo-ms-api-usage-and-parameter-configuration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Each row represents a sample and columns encode the occurrence counts of MS2 peaks and neutral losses",
