      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/ms2-spectra-parsing-and-loading/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For both methods, features' MS/MS spectra are first binned and neutral losses relative to the precursor losses are calculated to build so-called documents using the spec2vec package (Spectrum to Document step). In (A1), occurrence of each word (peak or loss) in each spectra file (i.e., sample) is counted. Words are then extracted from their Document context and aggregated to build a MEMO vector for each sample (B). Samples' MEMO vectors can then be aligned to obtain a MEMO matrix (C).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes the workflow where spectra parsing is the first step before MEMO vector and matrix construction.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "ms2-spectra-parsing-and-loading",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use this skill as the first step before constructing a MemoMatrix",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:03:16.499699+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/multi-sample-metabolomics-data-integration/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Multiple MEMO vectors and/or MEMO matrices can be merged, facilitating the subsequent addition of supplementary samples' MEMO vectors. This is a convenient characteristic of the MEMO analytical workflow, which allows iterative analysis of evolving datasets",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms merging of MEMO vectors/matrices and retention-time-agnostic analysis, but does not explicitly name a 'merged_memo()' function or formally document a 'MemoMatrix' class with that exact name. The paper describes the conceptual capability and workflow but does not provide API-level function signatures.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "multi-sample-metabolomics-data-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Merges separately generated MS2 fingerprint matrices (MemoMatrix objects) from multiple metabolomics samples into a single unified matrix, enabling retention-time-agnostic comparative analysis across chemodiverse or cross-platform datasets.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:03:34.256540+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
