    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/multi-sample-metabolomics-data-integration/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "First, MS2 spectra are filtered and binned using matchms and spec2vec packages: peaks and losses to the precursor of the spectrum are converted into words",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms matchms is used for spectrum filtering and binning, but does not explicitly mention metadata cleaning or spectral format I/O as roles. The claim is broader than what the paper documents.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "multi-sample-metabolomics-data-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[role]",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "matchms role: 'Underlying library for MS2 spectrum handling, metadata cleaning, and spectral format I/O that MEMO depends on'",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:03:34.256540+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/multi-sample-metabolomics-data-integration/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In further developments, techniques relying on motifs in mass spectra, such as MS2LDA, could be adapted and used to retrieve common patterns in clustered samples (van der Hooft et al., 2016).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper does not describe spec2vec as a downstream tool for similarity scoring on merged fingerprints. spec2vec is used upstream in the MEMO workflow for document generation. The card's characterization of spec2vec's role appears to conflate it with other similarity-scoring tools mentioned elsewhere (e.g., cosine similarity in CSCS).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "multi-sample-metabolomics-data-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[role]",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "spec2vec role: 'Optional downstream tool for computing MS2 spectral similarity scores on merged fingerprints'",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:03:34.256540+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/multi-sample-metabolomics-data-integration/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Multiple MEMO vectors and/or MEMO matrices can be merged, facilitating the subsequent addition of supplementary samples' MEMO vectors... the addition of samples to a pre-existing dataset is straightforward... Despite these differences, both UMAP and TMAP visualizations present a clear clustering of the three additional Waltheria indica samples with the trypanocidal Melochia umbellata green stems extract of the global plant extract dataset",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates merging of MEMO matrices from samples acquired on different platforms and LC methods, confirming the core scope claim.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "multi-sample-metabolomics-data-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Merges separately generated MS2 fingerprint matrices from multiple metabolomics samples into a single unified matrix, enabling retention-time-agnostic comparative analysis across chemodiverse or cross-platform datasets.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:03:34.256540+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/multi-sample-metabolomics-data-integration/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To evaluate MEMO's ability to cluster similar samples affected by an alternative batch effect, explained this time by different MS platforms, we applied it to the evaluation dataset samples analyzed on a Q-Exactive Orbitrap (QE) and a Quadrupole-Time of Flight (Q-ToF) MS.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly demonstrates MEMO's capability to compare samples from different MS platforms (Q-Exactive and Q-ToF).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "multi-sample-metabolomics-data-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When to use: comparing samples acquired on different mass spectrometer technologies (e.g., MaXis Q-ToF vs Q-Exactive)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:03:34.256540+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/multi-sample-metabolomics-data-integration/010",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "This method is particularly suited for heterogeneous and chemodiverse sample sets... MEMO thus allows the comparison of vast ensembles of samples, even when analyzed over long periods of time, and on different chromatographic or mass spectrometry platforms.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms MEMO's ability to handle retention-time shifts and different LC methods without requiring RT-based alignment.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "multi-sample-metabolomics-data-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When to use: reconciling data from different LC methods with strong retention-time shifts",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:03:34.256540+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/multi-sample-metabolomics-data-integration/011",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper does not explicitly state when NOT to use MEMO or discuss scenarios where feature-level alignment would be preferable. This is a negative claim not addressed in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "null",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "multi-sample-metabolomics-data-integration",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: Input matrices are from the same LC\u2013MS run or cohort and have already been aligned at the feature level",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
