      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/per-sample-spectral-aggregation/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "peaks and losses to the precursor of the spectrum are converted into words (i.e. peak@mz and loss@mz) and grouped into so-called documents (Huber et al., 2020; Huber et al., 2021). Documents are then aggregated by summing peaks and losses occurrences across spectra of a given sample to obtain the MEMO vector",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes spec2vec converting peaks/losses into documents and words, but does not explicitly state that spec2vec learns structural relationships or creates embeddings. The paper focuses on document/word creation and aggregation, not embedding learning.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "per-sample-spectral-aggregation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[role]",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "spec2vec role: Converts aggregated peak and neutral loss counts into spectral embeddings; learns structural relationships between fragments for document-level vectorization",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:04:50.189270+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/per-sample-spectral-aggregation/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Spectra were processed using memo_ms v0.1.3... and the following parameters for spectra import were used: min_relative_intensity: 0.01, max_relative_intensity: 1, min_peaks_required: 10, losses_from: 10, losses_to: 200, n_decimals: 2.",
      "asbval:note": "MEMO (memo_ms package) integrates the full pipeline for sample vectorization with configurable parameters.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "per-sample-spectral-aggregation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[role]",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MEMO role: Implements the full MS2-based sample vectorization pipeline, integrating matchms and spec2vec for per-sample fingerprint generation and downstream visualization",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:04:50.189270+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/per-sample-spectral-aggregation/010",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The MS data were converted from. RAW (Thermo) standard data format to. mzXML format using the MSConvert software, part of the ProteoWizard package",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes conversion to mzXML format, not mzML. The paper also mentions .mgf (Mascot Generic Format) as input: 'the only required input is a. mgf file for each sample (Mascot Generic Format, a text format commonly used to report fragmentation mass spectrometry data)' (passage 7). Primary input format is .mgf, not mzML.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "per-sample-spectral-aggregation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "inputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MS2 spectra files in mzML",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:04:50.189270+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/principal-coordinate-analysis-interpretation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "These MEMO vectors can then be aligned and used for classical multivariate analysis (PCA, PCoA) and/or other dimensionality reduction approaches such as UMAP or TMAP (McInnes et al., 2018; Probst and Reymond 2020), allowing the efficient calculation and visualization of spectral relationships within large cohorts of samples.",
      "asbval:note": "PCoA is explicitly mentioned as a dimensionality reduction technique applied to MEMO vectors (MS2 fingerprints) for visualization. The paper demonstrates PCoA's use in comparing samples despite RT shifts and batch effects.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "principal-coordinate-analysis-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "PCoA reduces pairwise sample distances from MS2 fingerprint vectors to 2D coordinates for visual comparison of metabolomics samples. It enables identification of sample clusters and compositional similarities when retention time alignment or feature overlap is poor.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:05:11.057721+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/principal-coordinate-analysis-interpretation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The distance matrices were computed using pdist function ('braycurtis' metric) from scipy package (1.7.1) and scikit-bio (0.5.6) was used for PCoA computation on the resulting distance matrix",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly uses PCoA on distance matrices computed from MEMO vectors (MS2 fingerprints).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "principal-coordinate-analysis-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "PCoA reduces pairwise sample distances from MS2 fingerprint vectors to 2D coordinates for visual comparison of metabolomics samples.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:05:11.057721+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/principal-coordinate-analysis-interpretation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MEMO thus allows the comparison of vast ensembles of samples, even when analyzed over long periods of time, and on different chromatographic or mass spectrometry platforms... The MEMO strategy exploits the advantages of LC, namely its separative power (thus simplifying the chemical complexity of the analyzed sample and allowing isomerism resolving) while avoiding the caveats of a RT based alignment since the MEMO vectors only contain mass spectrometric information.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates PCoA's effectiveness on MEMO vectors across different LC methods, MS platforms, and with strong RT shifts.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "principal-coordinate-analysis-interpretation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Particularly valuable when samples are chemically diverse (poor feature overlap), acquired across different LC methods or mass spectrometer platforms, or subject to strong retention time shifts that preclude traditional feature-based comparison.",
