    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-format-parsing-and-validation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "First, MS2 spectra are filtered and binned using matchms and spec2vec packages: peaks and losses to the precursor of the spectrum are converted into words (i.e. peak@mz and loss@mz) and grouped into so-called documents",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms matchms is used for spectral parsing and filtering, but does not explicitly mention validation of metadata, peak lists, or precursor ion information as a distinct step. The paper focuses on converting peaks/losses to 'words' rather than explicit validation. MGF format is mentioned as input, but mzML, mzXML, msp, JSON are not explicitly named in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-format-parsing-and-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Parse mass spectrometry spectral data from common file formats (mzML, mzXML, MGF, msp, JSON) and validate metadata, peak lists, and precursor ion information to ensure data integrity before downstream processing.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:07:06.612479+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-format-parsing-and-validation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "First, MS2 spectra are filtered and binned using matchms and spec2vec packages: peaks and losses to the precursor of the spectrum are converted into words (i.e. peak@mz and loss@mz) and grouped into so-called documents (Huber et al., 2020; Huber et al., 2021).",
      "asbval:note": "matchms is confirmed to filter and bin spectra, but the paper does not explicitly state it parses/validates multiple formats (mzML, mzXML, msp, JSON). Only MGF is mentioned as input format. The role description overstates the scope of what the paper documents.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-format-parsing-and-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "matchms \u2014 Imports, parses, validates, and cleans MS/MS spectral metadata and peak lists from multiple file formats (mzML, mzXML, MGF, msp, JSON); enforces data quality before downstream processing.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:07:06.612479+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-format-parsing-and-validation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Spectra were processed using memo_ms v0.1.3 (https://pypi.org/project/memo-ms/0.1.3/) and the following parameters for spectra import were used: min_relative_intensity: 0.01, max_relative_intensity: 1, min_peaks_required: 10, losses_from: 10, losses_to: 200, n_decimals: 2.",
      "asbval:note": "memo-ms is explicitly used to process spectra and generate fingerprints via peak and loss counting. The tool is confirmed with version and parameters.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-format-parsing-and-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "memo-ms \u2014 Consumes validated Spectrum objects and their associated aligned feature tables to generate MS2 fingerprints via peak and neutral loss counting.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:07:06.612479+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-format-parsing-and-validation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "First, MS2 spectra are filtered and binned using matchms and spec2vec packages: peaks and losses to the precursor of the spectrum are converted into words (i.e. peak@mz and loss@mz) and grouped into so-called documents (Huber et al., 2020; Huber et al., 2021).",
      "asbval:note": "spec2vec is mentioned as used alongside matchms for converting peaks/losses to 'words' and grouping into documents. However, the paper does not explicitly describe spec2vec computing 'spectral embeddings and similarity scores' \u2014 it is used for document generation. The role description may overstate the direct function of spec2vec in this workflow.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3389-fbinf-2022-842964",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-format-parsing-and-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "spec2vec \u2014 Uses parsed and validated spectra to compute spectral embeddings and similarity scores based on spectral relationships learned from MS/MS fragmentation patterns.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T22:07:06.612479+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-format-parsing-and-validation/004",
