      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Samples' MEMO vectors can then be aligned to obtain a MEMO matrix (Figure 1C). This way of building a MEMO matrix without prior RT based features alignment across samples is defined hereafter as 'MEMO from unaligned samples' approach (Figure 1A1).",
      "asbval:note": "The paper confirms that spectral data is parsed and used for fingerprint generation in the MEMO workflow. However, the scope description claims parsing of multiple formats (mzML, mzXML, msp, JSON) which are not all explicitly mentioned in the paper. Only MGF is explicitly named. The paper does not emphasize 'validation' as a distinct step, though filtering is mentioned.",
